~FT+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
~FT   Command~RS  : colour                                    ~FTRNUTS Version 3.0.2
~FT+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

~FT   Usage~RS    : colour

   This command toggles colour on and off.  The colour itself is 
   controlled by embedded tags in text strings which all begin with 
   a '~', eg /~FG.  They are the following...

   Control tags...  
  
     /~RS : Rest terminal to default state
     /~RV : ~RVReverse video
     /~OL : ~OLBold
     /~LI : ~LIBlink/flash text. This only works on some terminals, 
           ~LIothers may simply display it as bold.
     /~UL : ~ULUnderline text. As with blink this doesn't work on all 
           ~ULterminals, some just display it as bold.

   Foreground colour tags...              Background colour tags... 

     /~FK : ~FK~BWForeground black~RS~FW             /~BK : Background black
     /~FM : ~FMMagenta/purple       ~FW        /~BM : ~BMMagenta/purple
     /~FR : ~FRRed                  ~FW        /~BR : ~BRRed
     /~FY : ~FYYellow/orange        ~FW        /~BY : ~BYYellow/orange
     /~FG : ~FGGreen                ~FW        /~BG : ~BGGreen
     /~FB : ~FBBlue                 ~FW        /~BB : ~BBBlue
     /~FT : ~FTTurquoise/bright blue~FW        /~BT : ~BTTurquoise/bright blue
     /~FW : ~FWWhite                        /~BW : ~BW~FKWhite~RS

   So this: "/~FG/~BB/~LIhello world" would produce ~FG~BB~LIhello world
  
   To display the colour tags as themselves without them producing a 
   colour prepend the ~ with a / , eg //~FG

~FT+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
